Comment: I liked open games at the time.
Always. I was anticipating a Ruy Lopez.
Looking back with 20 years of hindsight, not the best move J. B. could have played.
I'm guessing he intended 4...P-Q4, shutting off the Bishop.
What the hell, may as well be adventurous.
That infamous lightning-stroke, Q-R5 ch, shows up again.
5...P-N3 wouldn't help much... though it would have stopped the immediate checkmate. [5...P-N3 6 QxKP ch followed by 7 QxR would have supplied me with a winning material advantage.]
We barely sat down, and the game is over.
